Review:
This is a near perfect soundboard  recording that is good enough quality to be an official release. The show is amazing and deserves a place in even the smallest Dylan collection. If one should pick it apart for the minor irregularities, it would be that while the cover aesthetics are nice, some may find the purple on purple type a bit difficult to read. Also, as the original recording was obviously analog, there is slight tape hiss evident in the high-end. To some  ears, this hiss is an undesirable noise. These are the same folks who argue the benefits of digital recording over analog. This problem was eliminated five years earlier on the Swingin' Pig release: 'Now Ain't the Time for Your Tears'
